text.tspan: - clean up the click handling in ViewController
v style should just be levels and colors
- plus dashes and arrows for links
v Create Objs that can be parented
- Objs and Instances are the same
- Structure of instances will be built and destroyed by the Component
- Fundamental edits will be applied to the lowest Obj
- Others will be applied to the element, with option to apply them to the master
- objs are flat, filled with objs and instances
- refLinks (ref's links that have been cloned)
- instance root has own instance id
- instance of instance should reference the one that instance
- on instance base edit, edit the obj
- copy all instances (and their path) of the same obj
- save to a temp ref obj
- find the difference of path from original parent to the new one
- apply the same change to the ids in the temp ref obj
- when new instances are created, check the temp ref for matching id, and copy state if exists
- link between objs/instances is cloned to link between instances with the same id transform (if found)
- cloned links are the same link object
- if an obj/instance finds a matching pair, it adds itself and the pair to the link
- when removed, also remove self and the pair from link
- link checks if both objs in a pair are not hidden before rendering that instance
- if a link has no objs, it deletes itself
- rect selection by checking rect of all instances
- when an instance is put into another, only allow when the level is lower
- when changing level, only allow to be lower than parent and higher than children
- for each mutation, if recording, add copy of the state
- on undo/redo just completely replace the state
- for the text, use hidden component for each master to facilitate searching, resulting in highlights
- when obj is not selected, use a div that can be split to multiple, highlighted spans
- when searching, use the master components and the obj text spans
- add multi search for multi highlights with different colors
- split search term to highlight partial matches
- when replacing, replace the text in the master directly
- when selecting 1 obj, also search and highlight (in the background)
- when an instance component can't find its ref
